 Kadzhaya (Moscow) - for the book \u201cDeacon The Shameless, or How Do They Make Anti-Semite\u201d|accessdate=October 1, 2018|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20140825073554/http://ruj.ru/docs/080202.html|archivedate=August 25, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\u0412\u0430\u043b\u0435\u0440\u0438\u0439 \u0413\u0435\u043e\u0440\u0433\u0438\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u041a\u0430\u0434\u0436\u0430\u044f - \u0414\u0438\u0430\u043a\u043e\u043d \u0431\u0435\u0441\u0441\u0442\u044b\u0436\u0438\u0439, \u0438\u043b\u0438 \u043a\u0430\u043a \u0434\u0435\u043b\u0430\u044e\u0442 \u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0435\u043c\u0438\u0442\u043e\u043c - \u041c\u043e\u0436\u043d\u043e \u043b\u0438 \u043d\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0434\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u0442\u044c 8 \u041c\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430, \u0438\u043b\u0438 \u043a\u0430\u043a \u0435\u0432\u0440\u0435\u0439\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u041f\u0443\u0440\u0438\u043c \u0441\u0442\u0430\u043b \u043c\u0435\u0436\u0434\u0443\u043d\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043d\u044b\u043c \u0436\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u043c \u0434\u043d\u0435\u043c. \u0410\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0442\u0430\u0446\u0438\u044f|trans-title=Valery G. Kadzhaya - Deacon The Shameless, or How Do They Make Anti-Semite - Is it possible not to celebrate March 8, or how Jewish [[Purim]] became an [[International Women's Day]]. Annotation |url=http://esxatos.com/kadzhaya-diakon-besstyzhiy-ili-kak-delayut-antisemitom |website=esxatos.com |publisher=\u0395\u03a3\u03a7\u0391\u03a4\u039f\u03a3 |accessdate=2 April 2020 |quote=Kuraev\u2019s book can be disassembled chapter by chapter, page by page. Everywhere there are lies, distortions, juggling. It's is like a corrupt anchor. But after all, someone \"will poison his poisoned arrows with that poison\"? The saddest thing,  this book (both the 1st and 2nd editions) is sold only in churches and church shops. Thus, the lie of Kuraev is supported not only by the authority of the printed word, the priesthood and academic degrees of the author, but also by the authority of the Russian Orthodox Church, and this, I think, is the most important danger}}</ref> The same year he's called Madonna a [[Profanity|curse word]]  \"[[Mat (Russian profanity)#Bly\u00e1d'|blyad']]\" ({{lang-rus|\u0431\u043b\u044f\u0434\u044c}}; modern meaning is something between \"whore\" {{lang-rus|\u0448\u043b\u044e\u0445\u0430|shloycha}}, \"bitch\" {{lang-rus|\u0441\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0432\u0430|sterva}}, and the closest local analogue of profane F word similarly [[Euphemism|euphemized]] as \"the word starting with b\" {{lang-rus|\u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u0431\u0443\u043a\u0432\u0443 \"\u0431\"|slovo na bukvu be}}. E. g. [[Anton Chekhov]] wrote in his 1889 letter: \"For no purpose, you have left [[Marina Mnishek]]. Of all the historical little harlots ({{lang-rus|\u0431\u043b\u044f\u0434\u0438\u0448\u0435\u043a|blyadishek}})<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.languagestepbystep.com/2017/06/23/50-shades-of-cute-diminutive-suffixes-of-russian-nouns-part-1/|title=\"Fifty Shades Of Cute\": Diminutive Russian Nouns|publisher=Language Step by Step|quote=\u2013shek is a diminutive suffix of many nouns [female plural and masculine singular suffixes are identical in this case]|accessdate=November 4, 2019}}</ref> (rhyme to Mnishek), she is perhaps the most colorful one\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.classicalmusicnews.ru/articles/anton-gopko-boris-godunov-5/|title=Across the pages of Boris Godunov: From Jesuitism to Foolishness, or Two Worlds - Two Systems|publisher=Classical Music News|language=Russian|date= April 14, 2010|accessdate=November 3, 2019}}</ref>) during [[Radio Mayak]] broadcast, also quoting his meaning for the word is \"wrong\" ([[heretic]]) in [[Church Slavonic language]], which caused a scandal. Later that year he defended his use of the word by misquoting \"Roman blyad\" (meaning Roman Catholic Church) from [[Avvakum|protopope Avvakum]] autobiography as \"Nikon's blyads\" (meaning the supporters of [[Patriarch Nikon of Moscow|Patriarch Nikon]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xoTdNIEhZPY|title=\u0414\u044c\u044f\u043a\u043e\u043d \u0410\u043d\u0434\u0440\u0435\u0439 \u041a\u0443\u0440\u0430\u0435\u0432 \u043e \"\u0431\u043b\u044f\u0434\u0438\" \u043f\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0446\u0435 \u041c\u0430\u0434\u043e\u043d\u043d\u0435|trans-title=Deacon Andrei Kuraev about the \"blyad\" singer Madonna|publisher= [[YouTube]]|date=October 4, 2008|accessdate=January 6, 2019|language=Russian}}</ref> In 2012, the deacon condemned the use of the word by Deputy Prime Minister of Russia [[Dmitry Rogozin]] considering Madonna's supoort of Pussy Riot as the official's try on PR.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://life.ru/t/%D0%BD%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%BE%D1%81%D1%82%D0%B8/99158|title=\u041a\u0443\u0440\u0430\u0435\u0432: \u0420\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0437\u0438\u043d \u0440\u0435\u0448\u0438\u043b \u043f\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0438\u0430\u0440\u0438\u0442\u044c\u0441\u044f \u043d\u0430 \u041c\u0430\u0434\u043e\u043d\u043d\u0435|trans-title=Kuraev: Rogozin decided to promote on Madonna|publisher=Life.ru|date=August 9, 2012|language=Russian|accessdate=October 9, 2019}}</ref> Before her concert in Moscow Madonna expressed her opinion on [[Freedom of religion in Russia|Russian state-church relations]] in a ''[[Kommersant]]'': \"I am convinced that the church and the government should not be together, they must exist separately. When they are together, it's a very dangerous marriage. Other countries have experienced this problem, and we know that a situation when church and state are too close will harm everyone in the end. I believe in democracy. Nonetheless, Russia should become a democratic country after having said goodbye to [[communism]]. That's how it should be!<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kommersant.ru/doc/1996968|title=\"\u041d\u0430\u0432\u0435\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0435, \u0441\u0442\u043e\u0438\u043b\u043e \u0443\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u0438\u0432\u0430\