50)|trans-title=Film \"Mussorgsky\" (1950)|quote=It's curious that Modest Petrovich didn't have a habit of refining the tunes for a long time, making edits or drafts. He carefully thought over ideas, and then sat down to record a completely finished music|language=Russian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://arzamas.academy/materials/1375|title=\u0427\u0430\u0439\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0438 \"\u041c\u043e\u0433\u0443\u0447\u0430\u044f \u043a\u0443\u0447\u043a\u0430\": \u0441\u043f\u043e\u0440 \u043e \u0440\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043c\u0443\u0437\u044b\u043a\u0435|trans-title=Tchaikovsky and The Mighty Handful: A Debate About Russian Music|quote=Under the influence of these ideas, the source of which was largely French naturalism, new images from the social lower classes emerge in Mussorgsky\u2019s works as \u201chigh\u201d music - for example, the Holy Fool in opera 'Boris Godunov' and in vocal monologue 'Svetik Savishna', or a homeless child asking alms, in the vocal composition \"Orphan\"|publisher=Arzamas Academy|accessdate=November 22, 2019|language=Russian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mussorgsky.ru/hubov134.html|title=\u0413\u043b\u0430\u0432\u0430 VI. \u0420\u0443\u0431\u0438\u043a\u043e\u043d|trans-title=Part VI. Rubicon|publisher=Mussorgsky.ru Project|quote=From the refrain, the \u201c[[List of compositions by Modest Mussorgsky|Yeryomushka's Lullaby]]\u201d is long drawn out (in the [[Dorian mode]]) as: \u201cYou have to bend your head below a thin grass [level] so that [you,] a poor orphan will live a blithely life\u201d. Combined with the music, these words sound like a secret murmur of the humiliated and destitute|language=Russian}}</ref> Mussorgsky's music was called \"rubbish\" ({{lang-rus|\u043c\u0443\u0441\u043e\u0440|musor|\u02c8mus\u0259r}}) by contemporary Russian critics, and his opera ''[[Boris Godunov (opera)|Boris Godunov]]'' was personally banned by the [[House of Romanov]] monarchs for its strong democratic ideas (see also \"[[Tall poppy syndrome]]\").<ref>{{cite web|url=https://zen.yandex.ru/media/kultshpargalka/kogo-ne-hvataet-na-kartine-repina-slavianskie-kompozitory-5d3b7005c31e4900add65774|title=\u041a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043d\u0435 \u0445\u0432\u0430\u0442\u0430\u0435\u0442 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0435 \u0420\u0435\u043f\u0438\u043d\u0430 \"\u0421\u043b\u0430\u0432\u044f\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u043a\u043e\u043c\u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u043e\u0440\u044b\"?|trans-title=Who is missing in Repin's painting 'Slavic Composers'?|quote=You will sweep away any rubbish into this picture!|language=Russian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.classic-music.ru/godunov.html|title=Opera \"Boris Godunov\"|quote=[[Alexander III of Russia|Alexander III]] and [[Nicholas II of Russia|Nicholas II]] have cancelled it from the repertoire of the Imperial theaters|publisher=Classic-music.ru|language=Russian}}</ref> In 2012, Madonna was accused of undermining Russia's defense in St. Petersburg.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.ru/news/219079-piterskie-pravoslavnye-obvinili-madonnu-v-podryve-oboronosposobnosti-rossii|title=\u041c\u0430\u0434\u043e\u043d\u043d\u0443 \u043e\u0431\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u0432 \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0440\u044b\u0432\u0435 \u043e\u0431\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u043e\u0441\u043f\u043e\u0441\u043e\u0431\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438|trans-title=Madonna was accused of undermining Russia's defense|publisher=[[Forbes]] Russia|date=2012-11-22|language=Russian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://aif.ru/society/history/kuharkiny_deti_kak_zakon_v_sfere_obrazovaniya_privyol_k_krusheniyu_imperii|title=\"\u041a\u0443\u0445\u0430\u0440\u043a\u0438\u043d\u044b \u0434\u0435\u0442\u0438\". \u041a\u0430\u043a \u0437\u0430\u043a\u043e\u043d \u0432 \u0441\u0444\u0435\u0440\u0435 \u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0437\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0432\u0451\u043b