/733447-madonna-sovetuet-pussy-riot-byit-chestnyimi-pered-samimi-soboy.html|title=\u041c\u0430\u0434\u043e\u043d\u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0442\u0443\u0435\u0442 Pussy Riot \"\u0431\u044b\u0442\u044c \u0447\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043d\u044b\u043c\u0438 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0434 \u0441\u0430\u043c\u0438\u043c\u0438 \u0441\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0439\"!|trans-title=Madonna advises [[Pussy Riot]] \"to be honest with themselves!\"|publisher=[[\u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043a\u043e\u043c\u0441\u043e\u043c\u043e\u043b\u0435\u0446|\u041c\u041a]]|date=August 6, 2012|accessdate=June 5, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140917051225/http://www.mk.ru/culture/2012/08/05/733447-madonna-sovetuet-pussy-riot-byit-chestnyimi-pered-samimi-soboy.html|archivedate=September 17, 2014|quote=Liz Rozenberg: I personally have never seen \u201ccurrents of negative criticism\u201d.|url-status=live|language=Russian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://ria.ru/20190625/1555912778.html|title=\u041c\u0430\u0434\u043e\u043d\u043d\u0430 \u0432\u043d\u043e\u0432\u044c \u0432\u043e\u0437\u0433\u043b\u0430\u0432\u0438\u043b\u0430 \u0430\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0438\u043a\u0430\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0445\u0438\u0442-\u043f\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0434|trans-title=Madonna Topped the US Chart Again|publisher=[[RIA Novosti]]|date=June 26, 2019|accessdate=June 26, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626204601/https://ria.ru/20190625/1555912778.html|archivedate=June 26, 2019|language=Russian|quote=Music critics [of the West] gave the album an icy welcome}}</ref> In the 2015 book \"''[[Pugachev's Rebellion|Pugachiovs\u0441shina]]: the end of story''\", the well-known Soviet and [[Belarusians|Belarusian]] composer [[Eduard Khanok]] has pointed out the misunderstanding of the Russian people which is served by the genre critics: \"People always confuse classical music with pop. In classical music, there's an accurate classification of voices: tenor, soprano, mezzo-soprano, etc. Estrada (show business) is a diversity of sounds: from \u201csweet-voiced\u201d [...] to \u201cvoiceless\u201d [...]. Classical voices compete who's better at performing the well-known pieces from [[Tchaikovsky]], [[Verdi]]... In Estrada (show business) everyone comes with their own \u201c*hit\u201d [material], excuse me, \u2014 with their baggage. Most of the time, then they leave with it for nowhere. And the performer's task on stage is to try to stand out from the crowd, find its face, the repertoire. Therefore, the main thing in this profession is not the voice but the image. The voice should be just good enough not to spoil the image\". The book title \"Pugachiovs\u0441shina\" is a reference to Alla Pugacheva. According to Khanok, who was a student of famous classical composer and teacher [[Dmitry Kabalevsky]] at Moscow Conservatory,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kp.by/daily/25643.3/806723/|title=\u042d\u0434\u0443\u0430\u0440\u0434 \u0425\u0410\u041d\u041e\u041a: \"\u042f \u0431\u044b\u043b \u0441\u0430\u043c\u044b\u043c \u0431\u043e\u0433\u0430\u0442\u044b\u043c \u0431\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u0438\u043c \u043a\u043e\u043c\u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043c\"|trans-title=Eduard KHANOK: \u201cI was the richest Belarusian composer\u201d|publisher=[[Komsomolskaya pravda]] Belarus|date=February 24, 2011|accessdate=October 9, 2019|language=Russian}}</ref> the decreased quality of a local song industry is a result of her natural human desire to monetize already huge fame as a performer a lot more effectively: to gain royalties as a composer without either melodic gift or professional education by singing the lower quality self-composed songs and then promoting them through abusing the power connections<ref>{{cite web |last1=Goncharov |first1=Vladislav |title=\u00ab\u0423 \u0410\u043b\u043b\u044b \u0435\u0441\u0442\u044c \u0430\u043a\u0446\u0438\u0438, \u043d\u043e \u0443\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043b\u044f\u0435\u0442 \u0438\u043c\u0438 \u0434\u0440\u0443\u0433\u043e\u0439\u00bb: \u0421\u043e\u0441\u0435\u0434\u043e\u0432 \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0434\u0438\u043b \u043d\u0435\u0444\u0442\u044f\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0431\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0441 \u041f\u0443\u0433\u0430\u0447\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0439 |trans-title= \u201cAlla has shares, but another controls them\u201d: Sosedov confirms Pugacheva\u2019s oil business|url=https://radiokp.ru/znamenitosti/u-ally-est-akcii-no-upravlyaet-imi-ne-ona-sosedov-podtverdil-neftyanoy-biznes-pugachevoy_nid16447_au4311au |publisher=[[Komsomolskaya Pravda]] Radio |accessdate=2 April 2020 |quote=She has always had high-ranking fans. The [[KGB]] general patronized her. And why do you think she behaved so freely? [Because] she could sing and say what she wants!}}</ref>{{sfn|Khanok|2015|p=132\u2014133}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pakhmutova.ru/songs/as020805.shtml|title=\u041f\u0430\u0445\u043c\u0443\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0443 \u0438 \u0414\u043e\u0431\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u043d\u0435 \u043f\u0443\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044e\u0442 \u0432 \u0448\u043e\u0443-\u0431\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0441|trans-title=Pakhmutova and Dobronravov are not allowed in show business|publisher=[[Trud (Russian newspaper)|Trud]]|date=August 2, 2005|accessdate=October 8, 2019|language=Russian|quote=There are certain recipes in our business on how to make a popular song that will make money. This can be compared to flirting. So, some young man, handsome, but with a cold heart, knowing certain tricks, can make a girl fall in love to get her for a one-night stand... I believe, for a true composer it is better to avoid this}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://rg.ru/2004/11/04/pahmutova.html|title=\u0417\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0430 \u043d\u0430\u0448\u0430 \u0442\u0430\u043a\u0430\u044f... \u0423 \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0440\u044b \u041f\u0430\u0445\u043c\u0443\u0442\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0439 - \u044e\u0431\u0438\u043b\u0435\u0439|trans-title=Our concern is so ...Alexandra Pakhmutova Anniversary|date=November 4, 2004|quote=In my opinion, now all over the world money has gotten out of control and they dictate the rules of the game. Not only here, but everywhere. As I said, the laws of show business are very harsh|language=Russian}}</ref> \n \n{{external media\n \t\n| float    = left\n \t\n| clear     = \n \t\n| width     = 440px\n \t\n|image1   = [https://laberintogris.com/9105-large_default/luis-royo-laberinto-gris-fantastic-art-mist-s-edge.jpg 2004 art] of Madonna as [[Valkyrie]] with [[elf]] ears in \u00abMist's Edge\u00bb by the Spanish artist [[Luis Royo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.luisroyo.com/en/biography/|title=Biography|publisher=Official site of Luis Royo |accessdate=2019-04-01|language=en|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402004710/http://www.luisroyo.com/en/biography/|archivedate=2019-04-02}}</ref> <small>In 2009 it has inspired the popular fan video for the song \"Olga\" (2003), music by [[Natalia O'Shea]], lyrics contain [[Nikolay Gumilev]]'s poem \"Olga\" (1920) about the medieval trendsetter,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nalin.ru/russkij-zhenskij-menedzhment-knyaginya-olga-i-zhanna-d-ark-5854|title=\u0420\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0436\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043c\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0434\u0436\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442. \u041a\u043d\u044f\u0433\u0438\u043d\u044f \u041e\u043b\u044c\u0433\u0430 \u0438 \u0416\u0430\u043d\u043d\u0430 \u0414`\u0410\u0440\u043a|trans-title=Russian women's management. Princess Olga and [[Joan of Arc]]|publisher=\"Na Linii\" (On Line)|quote=Today's Russia occupies a leading position in the world in the number of female top managers: 40% of the total number|date=August 17, 2017|accessdate=December 30, 2019|language=Russian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://naslednick.online/rubric/history/history_5277.html|title=\u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u