 she had 6,28% and 6th overall place in 2019, with first woman in space [[Valentina Tereshkova]] on a 1st place.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://yougov.co.uk/topics/international/articles-reports/2015/01/30/most-admired-2015|title=World's most admired 2015: Angelina Jolie and Bill Gates|publisher=[[YouGov]]|date=January 1, 2015|accessdate=January 11, 2019|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/75LjESQWW?url=https://yougov.co.uk/topics/international/articles-reports/2015/01/30/most-admired-2015|archivedate=January 11, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://yougov.co.uk/topics/international/articles-reports/2018/04/11/worlds-most-admired-2018|title=World\u2019s most admired 2018|publisher=YouGov|date=April 11, 2018|accessdate=January 11, 2019|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/75Lj9uV9m?url=https://yougov.co.uk/topics/international/articles-reports/2018/04/11/worlds-most-admired-2018|archivedate=January 11, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8521899/taylor-swift-madonna-yougov-most-admired-women-list|title=Taylor Swift & Madonna Among YouGov's Most Admired Women List|publisher=Billboard|date=July 19, 2019|accessdate=August 2, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190802161231/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8521899/taylor-swift-madonna-yougov-most-admired-women-list|archivedate=August 2, 2019}}</ref> Since 2008, deacon Andrey Kuraev's textbook \"Fundamentals of Orthodox Culture\" was approved for schoolchildren. Deacon Kuraev considered himself a Russian nationalist but his views were often perceived as both anti-Catholic and anti-Semitic.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.ru/books?id=Se5NAQAAIAAJ|title=\u0414\u0438\u0430\u043a\u043e\u043d \u0431\u0435\u0441\u0441\u0442\u044b\u0436\u0438\u0439, \u0438\u043b\u0438 \u043a\u0430\u043a \u0434\u0435\u043b\u0430\u044e\u0442 \u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0435\u043c\u0438\u0442\u043e\u043c|trans-title=Deacon The Shameless, or How Do Make Make Anti-Semite|author=Kadjaya Valery|pages=191|year=2008|place=Moscow|isbn=978-5-8125-1027-5}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ruj.ru/docs/080202.html|title=\u041b\u0430\u0443\u0440\u0435\u0430\u0442\u044b \u043f\u0440\u0435\u043c\u0438\u0438 \u0421\u043e\u044e\u0437\u0430 \u0436\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 2007 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430|trans-title=Winners of the 2007 Union of Journalists of Russia Prize|publisher=Union of Journalists of Russia|quote=Special Prize \u201cFor the Journalism Book\u201d ... Valery Kadzhaya (Moscow) - for the book \u201cDeacon The Shameless, or How Do They Make Anti-Semite\u201d|accessdate=October 1, 2018|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20140825073554/http://ruj.ru/docs/080202.html|archivedate=August 25, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\u0412\u0430\u043b\u0435\u0440\u0438\u0439 \u0413\u0435\u043e\u0440\u0433\u0438\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u041a\u0430\u0434\u0436\u0430\u044f - \u0414\u0438\u0430\u043a\u043e\u043d \u0431\u0435\u0441\u0441\u0442\u044b\u0436\u0438\u0439, \u0438\u043b\u0438 \u043a\u0430\u043a \u0434\u0435\u043b\u0430\u044e\u0442 \u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0435\u043c\u0438\u0442\u043e\u043c - \u041c\u043e\u0436\u043d\u043e \u043b\u0438 \u043d\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0434\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u0442\u044c 8 \u041c\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430, \u0438\u043b\u0438 \u043a\u0430\u043a \u0435\u0432\u0440\u0435\u0439\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u041f\u0443\u0440\u0438\u043c \u0441\u0442\u0430\u043b \u043c\u0435\u0436\u0434\u0443\u043d\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043d\u044b\u043c \u0436\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u043c \u0434\u043d\u0435\u043c. \u0410\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0442\u0430\u0446\u0438\u044f|trans-title=Valery G. Kadzhaya - Deacon The Shameless, or How Do They Make Anti-Semite - Is it possible not to celebrate March 8, or how Jewish [[Purim]] became an [[International Women's Day]]. Annotation |url=http://esxatos.com/kadzhaya-diakon-besstyzhiy-ili-kak-delayut-antisemitom |website=esxatos.com |publisher=\u0395\u03a3\u03a7\u0391\u03a4\u039f\u03a3 |accessdate=2 April 2020 |quote=Kuraev\u2019s book can be disassembled chapter by chapter, page by page. Everywhere there are lies, distortions, juggling. It's is like a corrupt anchor. But after all, someone \"will poison his poisoned arrows with that poison\"? The saddest thing,  this book (both the 1st and 2nd editions) is sold only in churches and church shops. Thus, the lie of Kuraev is supported not only by the authority of the printed word, the priesthood and academic degrees of the author, but also by the authority of the Russian Orthodox Church, and this, I think, is the most important danger}}</ref> The same year he's called Madonna a [[Profanity|curse word]]  \"[[Mat (Russian profanity)#Bly\u00e1d'|blyad']]\" ({{lang-rus|\u0431\u043b\u044f\u0434\u044c}}; modern meaning is something between \"whore\" {{lang-rus|\u0448\u043b\u044e\u0445\u0430|shloycha}}, \"bitch\" {{lang-rus|\u0441\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0432\u0430|sterva}}, and the closest local analogue of profane F word similarly [[Euphemism|euphemized]] as \"the word starting with b\" {{lang-rus|\u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u0431\u0443\u043a\u0432\u0443 \"\u0431\"|slovo na bukvu be}}. E. g. [[Anton Chekhov]] wrote in his 1889 letter: \"For no purpose, you have left [[Marina Mnishek]]. Of all the historical little harlots ({{lang-rus|\u0431\u043b\u044f\u0434\u0438\u0448\u0435\u043a|blyadishek}})<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.languagestepbystep.com/2017/06/23/50-shades-of-cute-diminutive-suffixes-of-russian-nouns-part-1/|title=\"Fifty Shades Of Cute\": Diminutive Russian Nouns|publisher=Language Step by Step|quote=\u2013shek is a diminutive suffix of many nouns [female plural and masculine singular suffixes are identical in this case]|accessdate=November 4, 2019}}</ref> (rhyme to Mnishek), she is perhaps the most colorful one\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.classicalmusicnews.ru/articles/anton-gopko-boris-godunov-5/|title=Across the pages of Boris Godunov: From Jesuitism to Foolishness, or Two Worlds - Two Systems|publisher=Classical Music News|language=Russian|date= April 14, 2010|accessdate=November 3, 2019}}</ref>) during [[Radio Mayak]] broadcast, also quoting his meaning for the word is \"wrong\" ([[heretic]]) in [[Church Slavonic language]], which caused a scandal. Later that year he defended his use of the word by misquoting \"Roman blyad\" (meaning Roman Catholic Church) from [[Avvakum|protopope Avvakum]] autobiography as \"Nikon's blyads\" (meaning the supporters of [[Patriarch Nikon of Moscow|Patriarch Nikon]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xoTdNIEhZPY|title=\u0414\u044c\u044f\u043a\u043e\u043d \u0410\u043d\u0434\u0440\u0435\u0439 \u041a\u0443\u0440\u0430\u0435\u0432 \u043e \"\u0431\u043b\u044f\u0434\u0438\" \u043f\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0446\u0435 \u041c\u0430\u0434\u043e\u043d\u043d\u0435|trans-title=Deacon Andrei Kuraev about the \"blyad\" singer Madonna|publisher= [[YouTube]]|date=October 4, 2008|accessdate=January 6, 2019|language=Russian}}</ref> In 2012, the deacon condemned the use of the word by Deputy Prime Minister of Russia [[Dmitry Rogozin]] considering Madonna's supoort of Pussy Riot as the official's try on PR.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://life.ru/t/%D0%BD%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%BE%D1%81%D1%82%D0%B8/99158|title=\u041a\u0443\u0440\u0430\u0435\u0432: \u0420\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0437\u0438\u043d \u0440\u0435\u0448\u0438\u043b \u043f\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0438\u0430\u0440\u0438\u0442\u044c\u0441\u044f \u043d\u0430 \u041c\u0430\u0434\u043e\u043d\u043d\u0435|trans-title=Kuraev: Rogozin decided to promote on Madonna|publisher=Life.ru|date=August 9, 2012|language=Russian|accessdate=October 9, 2019}}</ref> Before her concert in Moscow Madonna expressed her opinion on [[Freedom of religion in Russia|Russian state-church relations]] in a ''[[Kommersant]]'': \"I am convinced that the church and the government should not be together, they must exist separately. When they are together, it's a very dangerous marriage. Other countries have experienced this problem, and we know that a situation when church and state are too close will harm everyone in the end. I believe in democracy. Nonetheless, Russia should become a democratic country after having said goodbye to [[communism]]. That's how it should be!<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kommersant.ru/doc/1996968|title=\"\u041d\u0430\u0432\u0435\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0435, \u0441\u0442\u043e\u0438\u043b\u043e \u0443\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u0438\u0432\u0430\u0442\u044c \u044d\u0442\u043e \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043d\u0435 \u0432 \u0446\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0438, \u0430 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0434 \u0446\u0435\u0440\u043a\u043e\u0432\u044c\u044e\" - \u041c\u0430\u0434\u043e\u043d\u043d\u0430 \u043e Pussy Riot|trans-title=\"Perhaps it was worth arranging this performance not in the church, but in front of the church.\" Madonna about Pussy Riot|publisher=Kommersant|date=August 7, 2012|accessdate=November 4, 2019|language=Russian}}</ref> Right after the events journalist [[Masha Gessen]] said: \"I think, she won't have concerts in Russia until the regime changes.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.svoboda.org/a/24671310.html|title=\u0416\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0441\u0442 \u041c\u0430\u0448\u0430 \u0413\u0435\u0441\u0441\u0435\u043d \u2013 \u043e \u041c\u0430\u0434\u043e\u043d\u043d\u0435 \u043a\u0430\u043a \u0433\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0434\u0430\u043d\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0430\u043a\u0442\u0438\u0432\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043a\u0435|publisher=[[Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty|Radio Svoboda]]|quote=\u042f \u0434\u0443\u043c\u0430\u044e, \u043f\u043e\u043a\u0430 \u043d\u0435 \u0441\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0441\u044f \u0432\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u044c, \u0443 \u043d\u0435\u0451 \u0431\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0448\u0435 \u043a\u043e\u043d\u0446\u0435\u0440\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u0432 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u