and peoples to this day, ''[[Russia]]'' is officially called {{lang-fi|Ven\u00e4j\u00e4}}, {{lang-et|Venemaa}}, and {{lang-lv|Krievija}} (see also Eastern [[Galindians]], Baltic people near Moscow completely assimilated as \"Pravoslavnye\" (Russian translation of Greek word \"Orthodox\" \u2014 {{lang-rus|\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u044b\u0435|pravoslavnye}}, is spelled and pronounced very similar to the word \"Proto-Slavic\" \u2014 {{lang-rus|\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u044f\u043d\u0435|praslavyane}}). The term \"Orthodox\" was perceived as an ethnical identity in [[Russian Empire]], and after collapse of a Soviet Union people were encouraged to list themselves as \"Orthodox\" in a polls, based on a fact of their origin from Russian peasants (Russian word \"peasant\" ({{lang-rus|\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0442\u044c\u044f\u043d\u0438\u043d|krest'yanin}}) is a term delivered from \"Christian\" ({{lang-rus|\u0445\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0430\u043d\u0438\u043d|christianin}})). Thus, Madonna's [[Harper's Bazaar]] quote about wearing a scarf \"like a Russian peasant\" can also be translated as \"like an Orthodox Christian\".</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/celebrity/latest/news/a1095/madonna-interview-1113/|title=Madonna's Back|publisher=[[Harper's Bazaar]]|date=October 4, 2013|accessdate=March 4, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190109174549/https://www.harpersbazaar.com/celebrity/latest/news/a1095/madonna-interview-1113/|archivedate=January 9, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|quote=Nobody could ever conquer Russia|title=\u0417\u0430\u0447\u0435\u043c \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0430 \u043e\u0442\u043c\u0435\u043d\u044f\u0435\u0442 \u043c\u043e\u043d\u0433\u043e\u043b\u043e-\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0430\u0440\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0435 \u0438\u0433\u043e?|trans-title=Why is Moscow denying the Mongol-Tatar yoke?|url=https://www.obozrevatel.com/abroad/zachem-moskva-otmenyaet-mongolo-tatarskoe-igo.htm|publisher=Obozrevatel.com (Ukraine)|date=January 23, 2018|accessdate=December 11, 2019|language=Russian}}.</ref><ref>{{cite web|quote=Therefore, when they ask me: \"What is Russian?\" - I do not know. I just say, they're similar to the Irish, in my opinion. \u201cTo the Irish ??\u201d - I say \"Yes\". Because the ups and downs of mood are typical - one. They like to drink - two. They like to fight - three. They like to have friends - four. Literary talent - five. All the great English writers are actually Irish. Almost all of them. And one more thing: there were a lot of victims. After all, the Irish suffered 800 years from the British! And the Russians - from the Tatars. And then, not only from the Tatars. And suffering adds something|url=https://pozneronline.ru/2018/07/21824/|title=\u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440 \u041f\u043e\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0440 \u043e \u0440\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u043e\u043c \u0447\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043a\u0435|trans-title=[[Vladimir Pozner Jr.|Vladimir Pozner]] about Russian personality|date=July 16, 2018|accessdate=December 12, 2019|language=Russian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.todayfm.com/muireann-oconnell/ten-times-madonna-proved-she-is-actually-irish-329889|title=Ten Times Madonna Proved She Is Actually Irish|publisher=Today FM|date=August 16, 2018|accessdate=December 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/science/2015/dec/28/origins-of-the-irish-down-to-mass-migration-ancient-dna-confirms|title=Irish DNA originated in Middle East and eastern Europe|publisher=Guardian|date=December 28, 2015|accessdate=December 12, 2019}}</ref> By coincidence, Madonna was using [[Cyrillic script|Cyrillyc letters]] as a decoration for her first performance with \"[[Everybody (Madonna song)|Everybody]]\" in the Danceteria, and her use of {{runic|\u16d7}} ([[Mannaz]]) [[Runic alphabet]] letter, as [[Madame X Tour]] logo.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ttJBJTcnroc|title=Everybody - live at the Danceteria|publisher=Official Madonna YouTube}}</ref> According to Chinese ''[[Sina Corp|Sina]]'', Europeans have historically perceived Russians as Asian people with [[Mongol]]ian blood.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://inosmi.ru/social/20190922/245855920.html|title=Sina (\u041a\u0438\u0442\u0430\u0439): \u0438\u0441\u043f\u043e\u043a\u043e\u043d \u0432\u0435\u043a\u043e\u0432 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u044f \u2013 \u0435\u0432\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0435\u0439\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0430, \u043d\u043e \u043f\u043e\u0447\u0435\u043c\u0443 \u0415\u0432\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0430 \u043e\u0442\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0438\u0442 \u0435\u0435 \u043a \u0410\u0437\u0438\u0438?|trans-title=[[Sina Corp|Sina]] (China): For centuries, Russia was a European country, but why does Europe attribute it to Asia?|quote=There is an old saying in Europe: scratch a Russian - you will find a Tatar. The expression says that Mongolian blood actually flows inside the Russians, therefore they should not be considered Europeans|publisher=Chinese \"Sina\" translated to Russian - Inosmi.ru|date=September 22, 2019|accessdate=December 11, 2019|language=Russian}}</ref> As for 2019, French President [[Emmanuel Macron]] was the minority thinking it's possible to reverse Russia's turn from the West to China which started from [[Russian gay propaganda law|2012 gay-propaganda law]], or earlier, with Putin's 2011 quote from ''[[The Jungle Book]]'''s character, python [[Kaa]]<ref group=\"note\">In Russia, [[Vladimir Putin]]'s self-confessed love for [[Rudyard Kipling]] was not considered as racist characteristics. Historically, the adapted translation of his poem ''[[The Ballad of East and West]]'' was a lot more popular than his ''[[:s:The Man Who Was|The Man Who Was]]'' (1890), beginning: \"Let it be clearly understood that the Russian is a delightful person till he tucks in his shirt. As an Oriental he is charming. It is only when he insists upon being treated as the most easterly of western peoples instead of the most westerly of easterns that he becomes a racial anomaly extremely difficult to handle. The host never knows which side of his nature is going to turn up next\".</ref>, or in June-August 2006, when the media turned public attention from Putin-kissed-a-boy incident to well-sponsored anti-Madonna protests.<ref>{{cite web |title=Nikita Konkin: Boy who Vladimir Putin kissed on the stomach speaks about the \u2018spontaneous\u2019 gesture |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/nikita-konkin-boy-who-vladimir-putin-kissed-on-the-stomach-speaks-about-the-spontaneous-gesture-a6829786.html |publisher=[[The Independent|Independent]] |accessdate=8 March 2020 |date=2016-01-23}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043e\u0440\u0433\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0437\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043b\u0438 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0443\u044e \u0430\u043a\u0446\u0438\u044e \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0434 \u043b\u043e\u0437\u0443\u043d\u0433\u0430\u043c\u0438 \u00abMadonna, go home\u00bb, \u00ab\u0411\u0438\u043b\u0430\u0439\u043d\u00bb \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0449\u0430\u0439!\u00bb (\u0424\u041e\u0422\u041e)|trans-title= Orthodox organizations held a new protest rally with slogans \"Madonna, go home\", \"Beeline\" goodbye! \" (PHOTO)|url=https://newdaynews.ru/moskow/82661.html |accessdate=8 March 2020 |language=Russian |date=2006-09-12 |quote=after Ovchinnikov\u2019s speech, an impromptu \u201cMadonna\u201d came out to the center of the lawn, a young girl in a terrible mask and a wig with horns}}</ref>]]\n\t\nIn 2014, Madonna posted: \"Russia. Ukraine. Venezuela .........., now France?!!!!! Fight [[fascism]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.express.co.uk/news/world/480164/Madonna-branded-Granny-Gaga-by-far-right-National-Front-in-France-in-fascism-row|title=Madonna branded Granny Gaga by far-right National Front in France in fascism row|publisher=[[Daily Express ]]|date=June 4, 2014|accessdate=September 6, 2019}}</ref> In 2015, the performer has officially announced she won't tour Russia ever again because pedophilia and homosexuality were basically put into one category by a 2013 state-federal \"gay propaganda\" law which evolved from a 2012 St. Petersburg law.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/article/2016/08/16/madonna-andy-cohen-ew-interview/|title=Madonna's Andy Cohen interview: EW's guest editor questions the queen of pop|publisher=[[Entertainment Weekly|EW]]|date=August 16, 2015|accessdate=August 25, 2018|quote=No. But that\u2019s okay. Why would I even want to perform in a place where being gay is [criminalized]?}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://radiovesti.ru/news/685408/ |title=\u0412 \u041c\u0412\u0414 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u0443\u0433\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u043d\u043e \u043d\u0430\u043a\u0430\u0437\u044b\u0432\u0430\u0442\u044c \u0437\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0430\u0433\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0443 \u0433\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0441\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0443\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0437\u043c\u0430|trans-title=The Ministry of Internal Affairs proposed to criminalize homosexuality propaganda| publisher=[[Vesti FM]] |date=October 19, 2017|accessdate=September 27, 2018|quote=\u0412 \u041c\u0412\u0414 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043b\u0430\u0433\u0430\u044e\u0442 \u0443\u0436\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0447\u0438\u0442\u044c \u043d\u0430\u043a\u0430\u0437\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0437\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0430\u0433\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0443 \u043f\u0435\u0434\u043e\u0444\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0438 \u0438 \u0433\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0441\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0443\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0437\u043c\u0430 \u0441\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0438 \u0434\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0439. [The Ministry of Internal Affairs proposes to reinforce the punishment for the promotion of pedophilia and homosexuality among children.]|language=Russian}}</ref> In 2019, school headmaster Eugene Yamburg shared his opinion on the results of state religious education: \"Not so long ago a fourth-grader from another city was transferred to my school. She studied at the gymnasium, where she introduced elective courses: Orthodoxy, Islam, Judaism, secular ethics. And the girl says to me: \u201cEugene Sanych, you can\u2019t imagine how fortunate it is that we are Orthodox.\u201d I say: \"No objection.\" \u201cBut you can\u2019t imagine how much do I hate the Catholics!\u201d I wonder: \u201cFor what?\u201d \u201cSo, they pray to the Primadonna!\u201d - the girl is indignant. Of course, I explained that the [[Primadonna (Alla Pugacheva song)|Primadonna]] is Alla Borisovna Pugacheva, and the Catholics are praying Madonna, the Orthodox Mother of God. The girl was amazed\".<ref>{{cite web|trans-title=It is generally accepted that the West has lost the bonds, the spirituality that we supposedly have|title=\"\u041f\u0440\u0438\u043d\u044f\u0442\u043e \u0434\u0443\u043c\u0430\u0442\u044c, \u0447\u0442\u043e \u0417\u0430\u043f\u0430\u0434 \u043f\u043e\u0442\u0435\u0440\u044f\u043b \u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u043f\u044b, \u0434\u0443\u0445\u043e\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044c, \u043a\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0440\u044b\u0435 \u043c\u044b \u044f\u043a\u043e\u0431\u044b \u0438\u043c\u0435\u0435\u043c\"|url=https://mel.fm/shkola/9302816-principal_yamburg|accessdate=October 9, 2019|language=Russian}}</ref> Since 2017, according to a new domestic violence law, violence against the close relatives has been transferred from a criminal case to an administrative offense.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.svoboda.org/a/30056816.html|title=\u0412 \u0415\u0421\u041f\u0427 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0437\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u0438\u0437\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0442\u044c \u0437\u0430\u043a\u043e\u043d \u043e \u0434\u043e\u043c\u0430\u0448\u043d\u0435\u043c \u043d\u0430\u0441\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0438 \u0432 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438|trans-title=ECHR called on to amend the law on domestic violence in Russia|publisher=Radio Svoboda|date=July 15, 2019|accessdate=December 11, 2019|language=Russian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://novayagazeta.ru/articles/2019/03/11/79831-o-zhenschinah-i-svobode|title=\u041e \u0436\u0435\u043d\u0449\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0445 \u0438 \u0441\u0432\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0434\u0435. \u041d\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0439 \u0444\u0435\u043c\u0438\u043d\u0438\u0437\u043c \u0432\u043c\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043e \u0440\u0430\u0432\u043d\u043e\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0438\u044f \u043e\u0431\u0435\u0449\u0430\u0435\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e \u0442\u0440\u0435\u0431\u043e\u0432\u0430\u0442\u044c \u043a\u043e\u043c\u043f\u0435\u043d\u0441\u0430\u0446\u0438\u044e \u0437\u0430 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0433\u0440\u0435\u0445|trans-title=About women and freedom. A new feminism, instead of equality, promises the right to demand compensation for [[original sin]]|publisher=[[Novaya gazeta]]|date=March 11, 2019|accessdate=December 28, 2019|quote=Homo sapiens, as all hominids, has the female body weight for about 80% of the bodyweight of the male, and this leads to the fact that the male is the leader in the family and the head in the pack. We have the only close relative, which is an exception, it is the [[bonobo]] monkey, aka pygmy chimpanzee. In bonobos, relationships within the collective are built primarily through homosexual relationships. 80% of these homosexual relationships are females, and although females in Bonovo also weight fewer than males, they rule the society. A flock of bonobos is led by a collective [[Central Committee]] of old wise females. This is the only one of the higher apes that really has matriarchy. Matriarchy is not detected in any of the human societies. These are fairy tales}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Modest-Mussorgsky-young.jpg|thumb|right|By coincidence, Madonna Ciccone and influential classical composer [[Modest Mussorgsky|Modest P. Mussorgsky]] (1839-1881) not only have [[House of Rurik]] ancestry in common<ref name=\"myheritage\"/> but also their denial of academic education worthiness (instinctive approach to music<ref>{{cite web|url=https://youtube.com/embed/9ODgYFJ_eDU?start=299|title=Madonna - MTV Ultrasound Inside 1998|publisher=Official Madonna YouTube}}, and the shared idea of marginalized people having a voice.</ref>)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ivi.ru/watch/26603|title=\u0424\u0438\u043b\u044c\u043c \"\u041c\u0443\u0441\u043e\u0440\u0433\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439\" (1950)|trans-title=Film \"Mussorgsky\" (1950)|quote=It's curious that Modest Petrovich didn't have a habit of refining the tunes for a long time, making edits or drafts. He carefully thought over ideas, and then sat down to record a completely finished music|language=Russian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://arzamas.academy/materials/1375|title=\u0427\u0430\u0439\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0438 \"\u041c\u043e\u0433\u0443\u0447\u0430\u044f \u043a\u0443\u0447\u043a\u0430\": \u0441\u043f\u043e\u0440 \u043e \u0440\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043c\u0443\u0437\u044b\u043a\u0435|trans-title=Tchaikovsky and The Mighty Handful: A Debate About Russian Music|quote=Under the influence of these ideas, the source of which was largely French naturalism, new images from the social lower classes emerge in Mussorgsky\u2019s works as \u201chigh\u201d music - for example, the Holy Fool in opera 'Boris Godunov' and in vocal monologue 'Svetik Savishna', or a homeless child asking alms, in the vocal composition \"Orphan\"|publisher=Arzamas Academy|accessdate=November 22, 2019|language=Russian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mussorgsky.ru/hubov134.html|title=\u0413\u043b\u0430\u0432\u0430 VI. \u0420\u0443\u0431\u0438\u043a\u043e\u043d|trans-title=Part VI. Rubicon|publisher=Mussorgsky.ru Project|quote=From the refrain, the \u201c[[List of compositions by Modest Mussorgsky|Yeryomushka's Lullaby]]\u201d is long drawn out (in the [[Dorian mode]]) as: \u201cYou have to bend your head below a thin grass [level] so that [you,] a poor orphan will live a blithely life\u201d. Combined with the music, these words sound like a secret murmur of the humiliated and destitute|language=Russian}}</ref> Mussorgsky's music was called \"rubbish\" ({{lang-rus|\u043c\u0443\u0441\u043e\u0440|musor|\u02c8mus\u0259r}}) by contemporary Russian critics, and his opera ''[[Boris Godunov (opera)|Boris Godunov]]'' was personally banned by the [[House of Romanov]] monarchs for its strong democratic ideas (see also \"[[Tall poppy syndrome]]\").<ref>{{cite web|url=https://zen.yandex.ru/media/kultshpargalka/kogo-ne-hvataet-na-kartine-repina-slavianskie-kompozitory-5d3b7005c31e4900add65774|title=\u041a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043d\u0435 \u0445\u0432\u0430\u0442\u0430\u0435\u0442 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0435 \u0420\u0435\u043f\u0438\u043d\u0430 \"\u0421\u043b\u0430\u0432\u044f\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u043a\u043e\u043c\u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u043e\u0440\u044b\"?|trans-title=Who is missing in Repin's painting 'Slavic Composers'?|quote=You will sweep away any rubbish into this picture!|language=Russian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.classic-music.ru/godunov.html|title=Opera \"Boris Godunov\"|quote=[[Alexander III of Russia|Alexander III]] and [[Nicholas II of Russia|Nicholas II]] have cancelled it from the repertoire of the Imperial theaters|publisher=Classic-music.ru|language=Russian}}</ref> In 2012, Madonna was accused of undermining Russia's defense in St. Petersburg.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.ru/news/219079-piterskie-pravoslavnye-obvinili-madonnu-v-podryve-oboronosposobnosti-rossii|title=\u041c\u0430\u0434\u043e\u043d\u043d\u0443 \u043e\u0431\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u0432 \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0440\u044b\u0432\u0435 \u043e\u0431\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u043e\u0441\u043f\u043e\u0441\u043e\u0431\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438|trans-title=Madonna was accused of undermining Russia's defense|publisher=[[Forbes]] Russia|date=2012-11-22|language=Russian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://aif.ru/society/history/kuharkiny_deti_kak_zakon_v_sfere_obrazovaniya_privyol_k_krusheniyu_imperii|title=\"\u041a\u0443\u0445\u0430\u0440\u043a\u0438\u043d\u044b \u0434\u0435\u0442\u0438\". \u041a\u0430\u043a \u0437\u0430\u043a\u043e\u043d \u0432 \u0441\u0444\u0435\u0440\u0435 \u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0437\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0432\u0451\u043b \u043a \u043a\u0440\u0443\u0448\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044e \u0438\u043c\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0438\u0438|trans-title=\"Cook's children.\" How did the education law caused the crash of Russian Empire|publisher=[[Argumenty i fakty]]|date=July 1, 2017|accessdate=September 5, 2019|quote=Thus, with the strict observance of this rule, gymnasiums and a professional gymnasiums will be freed from the arrival of children of coachmen, footmen, cooks, laundresses, small shopkeepers and the alikes, whose children, with the exception of those gifted with genial abilities, should not strive for secondary and higher education at all|language=Russian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://echo.msk.ru/blog/fedor/951266-echo/|title=\u0428\u043a\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0435 \u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0437\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0438 \u0433\u0440\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0442\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044c \u0432 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u043a 1917 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0443|trans-title=School education and literacy in Russia by 1917|publisher=[[Echo of Moscow]]|quote= By 1897, not counting Finland, the precent of half-literate (the ones who could read '''and/or''' write) was 21,1% (29,3% men and 13,1% women). ([[Russian Empire]] didn't count people who could read and write simultaneously (literate) as a separate category, in order to have a better overall numbers, so all the half-literate were written down under the term \"literate\"; See also {{ill|Literacy in pre-revolutionary Russia|ru|\u0413\u0440\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0442\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044c \u0432 \u0434\u043e\u0440\u0435\u0432\u043e\u043b\u044e\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438}})}}</ref>]]\n \nMadonna's music was reviewed mostly negatively by Russian critics who were stating another false argument about \"currents of negative criticism\" towards almost all Madonna albums from all the Western music critics.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mk.ru/culture/2012/08/05/733447-madonna-sovetuet-pussy-riot-byit-chestnyimi-pered-samimi-soboy.html|title=\u041c\u0430\u0434\u043e\u043d\u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0442\u0443\u0435\u0442 Pussy Riot \"\u0431\u044b\u0442\u044c \u0447\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043d\u044b\u043c\u0438 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0434 \u0441\u0430\u043c\u0438\u043c\u0438 \u0441\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0439\"!|trans-title=Madonna advises [[Pussy Riot]] \"to be honest with themselves!\"|publisher=[[\u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043a\u043e\u043c\u0441\u043e\u043c\u043e\u043b\u0435\u0446|\u041c\u041a]]|date=August 6, 2012|accessdate=June 5, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140917051225/http://www.mk.ru/culture/2012/08/05/733447-madonna-sovetuet-pussy-riot-byit-chestnyimi-pered-samimi-soboy.html|archivedate=September 17, 2014|quote=Liz Rozenberg: I personally have never seen \u201ccurrents of negative criticism\u201d.|url-status=live|language=Russian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://ria.ru/20190625/1555912778.html|title=\u041c\u0430\u0434\u043e\u043d\u043d\u0430 \u0432\u043d\u043e\u0432\u044c \u0432\u043e\u0437\u0433\u043b\u0430\u0432\u0438\u043b\u0430 \u0430\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0438\u043a\u0430\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0445\u0438\u0442-\u043f\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0434|trans-title=Madonna Topped the US Chart Again|publisher=[[RIA Novosti]]|date=June 26, 2019|accessdate=June 26, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626204601/https://ria.ru/20190625/1555912778.html|archivedate=June 26, 2019|language=Russian|quote=Music critics [of the West] gave the album an icy welcome}}</ref> In the 2015 book \"''[[Pugachev's Rebellion|Pugachiovs\u0441shina]]: the end of story''\", the well-known Soviet and [[Belarusians|Belarusian]] composer [[Eduard Khanok]] has pointed out the misunderstanding of the Russian people which is served by the genre critics: \"People always confuse classical music with pop. In classical music, there's an accurate classification of voices: tenor, soprano, mezzo-soprano, etc. Estrada (show business) is a diversity of sounds: from \u201csweet-voiced\u201d [...] to \u201cvoiceless\u201d [...]. Classical voices compete who's better at performing the well-known pieces from [[Tchaikovsky]], [[Verdi]]... In Estrada (show business) everyone comes with their own \u201c*hit\u201d [material], excuse me, \u2014 with their baggage. Most of the time, then they leave with it for nowhere. And the performer's task on stage is to try to stand out from the crowd, find its face, the repertoire. Therefore, the main thing in this profession is not the voice but the image. The voice should be just good enough not to spoil the image\". The book title \"Pugachiovs\u0441shina\" is a reference to Alla Pugacheva. According to Khanok, who was a student of famous classical composer and teacher [[Dmitry Kabalevsky]] at Moscow Conservatory,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kp.by/daily/25643.3/806723/|title=\u042d\u0434\u0443\u0430\u0440\u0434 \u0425\u0410\u041d\u041e\u041a: \"\u042f \u0431\u044b\u043b \u0441\u0430\u043c\u044b\u043c \u0431\u043e\u0433\u0430\u0442\u044b\u043c \u0431\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u0438\u043c \u043a\u043e\u043c\u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043c\"|trans-title=Eduard KHANOK: \u201cI was the richest Belarusian composer\u201d|publisher=[[Komsomolskaya pravda]] Belarus|date=February 24, 2011|accessdate=October 9, 2019|language=Russian}}</ref> the decreased quality of a local song industry is a result of her natural human desire to monetize already huge fame as a performer a lot more effectively: to gain royalties as a composer without either melodic gift or professional education by singing the lower quality self-composed songs and then promoting them through abusing the power connections<ref>{{cite web |last1=Goncharov |first1=Vladislav |title=\u00ab\u0423 \u0410\u043b\u043b\u044b \u0435\u0441\u0442\u044c \u0430\u043a\u0446\u0438\u0438, \u043d\u043e \u0443\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043b\u044f\u0435\u0442 \u0438\u043c\u0438 \u0434\u0440\u0443\u0433\u043e\u0439\u00bb: \u0421\u043e\u0441\u0435\u0434\u043e\u0432 \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0434\u0438\u043b \u043d\u0435\u0444\u0442\u044f\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0431\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0441 \u041f\u0443\u0433\u0430\u0447\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0439 |trans-title= \u201cAlla has shares, but another controls them\u201d: Sosedov confirms Pugacheva\u2019s oil business|url=https://radiokp.ru/znamenitosti/u-ally-est-akcii-no-upravlyaet-imi-ne-ona-sosedov-podtverdil-neftyanoy-biznes-pugachevoy_nid16447_au4311au |publisher=[[Komsomolskaya Pravda]] Radio |accessdate=2 April 2020 |quote=She has always had high-ranking fans. The [[KGB]] general patronized her. And why do you think she behaved so freely? [Because] she could sing and say what she wants!}}</ref>{{sfn|Khanok|2015|p=132\u2014133}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pakhmutova.ru/songs/as020805.shtml|title=\u041f\u0430\u0445\u043c\u0443\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0443 \u0438 \u0414\u043e\u0431\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u043d\u0435 \u043f\u0443\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044e\u0442 \u0432 \u0448\u043e\u0443-\u0431\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0441|trans-title=Pakhmutova and Dobronravov are not allowed in show business|publisher=[[Trud (Russian newspaper)|Trud]]|date=August 2, 2005|accessdate=October 8, 2019|language=Russian|quote=There are certain recipes in our business on how to make a popular song that will make money. This can be compared to flirting. So, some young man, handsome, but with a cold heart, knowing certain tricks, can make a girl fall in love to get her for a one-night stand... I believe, for a true composer it is better to avoid this}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://rg.ru/2004/11/04/pahmutova.html|title=\u0417\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0430 \u043d\u0430\u0448\u0430 \u0442\u0430\u043a\u0430\u044f... \u0423 \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0440\u044b \u041f\u0430\u0445\u043c\u0443\u0442\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0439 - \u044e\u0431\u0438\u043b\u0435\u0439|trans-title=Our concern is so ...Alexandra Pakhmutova Anniversary|date=November 4, 2004|quote=In my opinion, now all over the world money has gotten out of control and they dictate the rules of the game. Not only here, but everywhere. As I said, the laws of show business are very harsh|language=Russian}}</ref> \n \n{{external media\n \t\n| float    = left\n \t\n| clear     = \n \t\n| width     = 440px\n \t\n|image1   = [https://laberintogris.com/9105-large_default/luis-royo-laberinto-gris-fantastic-art-mist-s-edge.jpg 2004 art] of Madonna as [[Valkyrie]] with [[elf]] ears in \u00abMist's Edge\u00bb by the Spanish artist [[Luis Royo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.luisroyo.com/en/biography/|title=Biography|publisher=Official site of Luis Royo |accessdate=2019-04-01|language=en|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402004710/http://www.luisroyo.com/en/biography/|archivedate=2019-04-02}}</ref> <small>In 2009 it has inspired the popular fan video for the song \"Olga\" (2003), music by [[Natalia O'Shea]], lyrics contain [[Nikolay Gumilev]]'s poem \"Olga\" (1920) about the medieval trendsetter,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nalin.ru/russkij-zhenskij-menedzhment-knyaginya-olga-i-zhanna-d-ark-5854|title=\u0420\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0436\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043c\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0434\u0436\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442. \u041a\u043d\u044f\u0433\u0438\u043d\u044f \u041e\u043b\u044c\u0433\u0430 \u0438 \u0416\u0430\u043d\u043d\u0430 \u0414`\u0410\u0440\u043a|trans-title=Russian women's management. Princess Olga and [[Joan of Arc]]|publisher=\"Na Linii\" (On Line)|quote=Today's Russia occupies a leading position in the world in the number of female top managers: 40% of the total number|date=August 17, 2017|accessdate=December 30, 2019|language=Russian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://naslednick.online/rubric/history/history_5277.html|title=\u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0438 \u0420\u0443\u0441\u0438: \u043a\u043d\u044f\u0433\u0438\u043d\u044f \u041e\u043b\u044c\u0433\u0430 \u2013 \u043c\u0435\u0441\u0442\u044c \u0438 \u0441\u0432\u044f\u0442\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044c|trans-title=Rulers of Russia: Princess Olga - revenge and holiness|quote=And when we talk about Princess Olga, it is necessary to find an analogue in the later history of our country. This analogue is the famous Empress [[Catherine the Great]]|publisher=Orthodox Youth Pornal \"Heir\"|date=October 17, 2017|accessdate=December 30, 2019|language=Russian}}</ref> Varangian [[Olga of Kiev|Olga]] (of [[Gardariki]] ({{lang-non|{{noitalic|\u16b4\u16c5\u16b1\u16a6\u16c5\u16b1\u16c1\u16b4\u16c1}}}})) in full.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/embed/xwLMFDJRg_c|title=\u041c\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0430 - \u041e\u043b\u044c\u0433\u0430 (\u0414\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0433\u0430 \u0441\u043d\u0430. \u0410\u0443\u0434\u0438\u043e)|trans-title=Melnitsa - Olga (The Dream Path)|publisher={{ill|Navigator Records|ru|Navigator Records}}|date=April 17, 2012|accessdate=December 10, 2019|quote= Music by N. O'Shea (Hellawes), words by N. Gumilev}}</ref></small> Olga's portrait mosaic image is at [[St. Peter's Basilica|The Papal Basilica of St. Peter in the Vatican]], left from an altar, North transept.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vatican.va/various/basiliche/san_pietro/vr_tour/index-en.html|title=Virtual tour, Point 3. North transept|author=Vatican|work=Knyaginya Olga|accessdate=December 11, 2019|publisher=Vatican.va}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://nv.ua/ukraine/events/1000-let-so-dnya-smerti-vladimira-velikogo-5-maloizvestnyh-faktov-o-kievskom-knyaze-59335.html|title=1000 \u043b\u0435\u0442 \u0441\u043e \u0434\u043d\u044f \u0441\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0442\u0438 \u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440\u0430 \u0412\u0435\u043b\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e. 5 \u043c\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0438\u0437\u0432\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0444\u0430\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u043e \u043a\u0438\u0435\u0432\u0441\u043a\u043e\u043c \u043a\u043d\u044f\u0437\u0435 |trans-title=1000 Years Since the Vladimir the Great's Death. 5 Lesser Known Facts about Kievan Prince|accessdate=December 12, 2019|language=Russian}}</ref> <small>By coincidence, Madonna's bulldog had the same nickname<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.celebritypetnews.com/2015/news/is-madonnas-new-birthday-gift-a-responsible-idea/|title=Is Madonna\u2019s New Birthday Gift a Responsible Idea?|publisher=Celebritypetnews.com|date=November 10, 2015|accessdate=December 10, 2019}}</ref></small>\n|image2 =[https://cdn1.img.ria.ru/images/10568/11/105681147.jpg 2008 Madon'''NATO''' art] \u2013 Madonna as [[NATO]]'s music representative, [[caricature]] by [[RIA Novosti|RIA]] artist Vladimir Kremlyov<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ria.ru/photolents/20080414/104991252.html|title=\u0420\u0418\u0410 \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0438\u043a\u0430\u0442\u0443\u0440\u044b \u0434\u043d\u044f \u043e\u0442 \u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440\u0430 \u041a\u0440\u0435\u043c\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0430. \u0422\u043e\u043c II|date=2008-04-14|accessdate=2018-11-13|quote=\u0438\u0437\u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 21 \u0438\u0437 90}}</ref>\n|image3 = [http://duginart.com/tl_files/duginart/pictures_presentation/hamlet/hamlet_gertrude.jpg 2013 book art]: Madonna as [[Gertrude (Hamlet)|Gertrude]] from Shakespeare's ''Hamlet'' by {{ill|Andrey Dugin|de|Andrej Dugin}}. \"Gertruda\" ({{lang-rus|\u0413\u0435\u0440\u0442\u0440\u0443\u0434\u0430|Gertruda}}) is also a slang meaning \"[[Hero of Labour of the Russian Federation|Hero of Labour]]\"  ({{lang-rus|\u0413\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0439 \u0422\u0440\u0443\u0434\u0430|Geroy Truda}}), [[honorary title]] in Soviet and post-Soviet Russia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://duginart.com/biography.html|title=biography|publisher=Official site of Olga Dugina and Andrey Dugin|accessdate=April 1, 2019|language=en|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014803/http://duginart.com/biography.html|archivedate=April 2, 2019}}</ref><ref group=\"note\">In Russia, Shakespeare's \"Gertrude\" is periodically portrayed as a misunderstood female character of smart ruler ahead of her time: she suicides conciously by drinking Hamlet's poison in the end, mostly out of disappointment in her men. The concept is based on a theory the Danish throne in a play should be inherited by king's brother, not his son, as it was in Norway, mentioned by Shakespeare (or other medieval states, including neighbouring medieval Rus'). In a local popular provincial paradigm, Queen Gertrude just secures her son's position by marrying his unkle, the one who could possibly have another children by a new young wife and, thus, could make Hamlet's chances to inherit the throne as low as possible, but Hamlet's clinical misogyny destroys the dynasty [http://www.magalif.ru/coll_gamlet ] Since 1970s portrayal by [[Alla Demidova]], Gertrude's suicide has become a local cliche, and the part has become a stereotypical dream role for Russian theatre actresses, e. g. in a 2007 film ''[[Actress (2007 film)|Actress]]'': \"Demidova's Gertrude is obviously too weak for martial arts, but she can never be reconciled with herself. She turns murder into suicide. She drinks the poisoned wine as if she's seen the truth at the bottom of a glass\".[http://www.demidova.ru/theatre/whorses/whg_01.php ]</ref>\n|video1= [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OYC-tzFi2z8 2016 Figure-skating to] \"[[Music (Madonna song)|Music]]\" cover, skating performance by Olympic champion [[Tatiana Navka]]. Music for Madonna's movie ''[[W.E.|W./E.]]'', composed by [[Abel Korzeniowski]], was used by two [[2016 World Figure Skating Championships]] winners: Russian [[Evgenia Medvedeva]] (Ladies) and  French pair [[Gabriella Papadakis]] / [[Guillaume Cizeron]] (Ice dancing).\n| video2    = [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1Hg5t4a97ts 2018 song] \"\u0411\u043e\u0439 \u0411\u0430\u0431\u0430\" (''Boy Baba'', an idiom meaning \"Superwoman\" and play of words Boi/Boy where \"Boi\" means 'Battle') by the Russian band [[Aquarium (group)|Aquarium]].<br><small>The work was perceived as a homage to Madonna, especially her ''[[secretprojectrevolution]]'' era. 3:44 contains an animated image of people holding banners \"Boy Baba for [[Tsardom of Russia|Tsardom]]!\", \"Boy Baba of [[Patriarch of Moscow and all Rus'|all Rus']]\", etc.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://madonna.ru.com/en/articles/boy-baba-aquarium-grebenshikov-madonna|title=BOY BABA - \u0411\u0413 \u0441\u0434\u0435\u043b\u0430\u043b \u043e\u043c\u043c\u0430\u0436 \u041c\u0430\u0434\u043e\u043d\u043d\u0435|publisher=\u041d\u0435\u043e\u0444\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0444\u0430\u043d-\u0441\u0430\u0439\u0442 Madonna.ru.com|date=December 12, 2018|accessdate=April 16, 2019|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/77gYPLI25?url=https://madonna.ru.com/articles/boy-baba-aquarium-grebenshikov-madonna|archivedate=April 16, 2019|trans-title=BOY BABA - BG made a hommage to Madonna|language=Russian}}</ref> Bulls' pink ridges of the video is a reference to the same Gumilev poem.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EA4lARWgwk4|title=\u041c\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0430.\u041e\u043b\u044c\u0433\u0430|trans-title=Melnitsa \"Olga\"|publisher=YouTube Channel \"Hakuna Matata\"|date=September 26, 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://gumilev.ru/languages/669/|title=Olga (1920)|publisher=Nikolay Gumilev online|accessdate=September 19, 2019}}</ref></small>\n}}\n \t\nIn 2018, Soviet and Georgian singer [[Nani Bregvadze]] has expressed a popular version about \"not a very good singer and dancer\" Madonna \"making a catastrophic change to the Soviet stage\" by switching the emphasis from songs to the show.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://iz.ru/751548/natalia-vasileva/glavnymi-dlia-menia-byli-i-ostaiutsia-dusha-i-liubov|title=\"\u0413\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u044b\u043c\u0438 \u0434\u043b\u044f \u043c\u0435\u043d\u044f \u0431\u044b\u043b\u0438 \u0438 \u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u044e\u0442\u0441\u044f \u0434\u0443\u0448\u0430 \u0438 \u043b\u044e\u0431\u043e\u0432\u044c\"|trans-title=Soul and love  was and remain the main things for me |publisher=[[Izvestia]]|accessdate=2017-06-27|date=2018-06-05|language=Russian}}</ref>  The professional conservatory level [[musicology|problem-semantic]] analysis of ''[[Confessions on a Dance Floor]]'' called  \"''Madonna: Amazing Discoveries''\" (2005) presented an argument against the hypothesis: \"No, Confessions on a dance floor is not just a good album. This is a real dance [[symphony]]. [...] Each level of [[mode (music)|mode]] has its own, individual role that it carries through the entire album, all stages are in a complex relationship with each other. And this is not just amazing, it's unbelievable. What kind of music are you talking about? This is not [[Beethoven]], this is not [[Chopin]], this is Madonna, this is popular music, not just popular. Super-popular. [...] To combine an album of light dance music with one idea, one intonation, one mode system, to limit yourself into short [[pentatonic]] tunes instead of the wide and beautiful melodies that Madonna can sing so elegantly  (\"[[Don't Cry for Me Argentina|Don't cry for me, Argentina]]\", oh-oh-oh ....) How could one even conceive such thing, not to mention, and managed to embody that?\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://madonna.ru.com/memes/madonna-udivitelnye-otkrytiya|title=Madonna: \u0443\u0434\u0438\u0432\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043e\u0442\u043a\u0440\u044b\u0442\u0438\u044f|trans-title=Madonna: Amazing Discoveries|publisher= Conservatory student (pseudonym \u2013 Twinsen) Article saved on Unofficial Fan Site Madonna.RU.com|date=December 16, 2005|accessdate=October 8, 2019|language=Russian}}</ref> In 2009, Russian musicologist, [[Moscow Conservatory]] professor, [[Marina Karaseva]] has also noticed an almost complete unpreparedness of Russian audience for the perception of Madonna's work on a concert: \"Apparently, our listeners-spectators need to \u201crise above themselves\u201d for a long time, and not to relax themselves on the consumption of domestic poppy pop music of any dignity which feels it's safe\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://inbedwithmadonna.ru/post97675540/|title=\u041f\u0423\u0413\u0410\u0427\u0415\u0412\u0410 \u0414\u0416\u0415\u041a\u0421\u041e\u041d \u041c\u0410\u0414\u041e\u041d\u041d\u0410|publisher=Portal Kommentarii.ru |date=March 7, 2009|accessdate=November 29, 2018|archivedate=February 15, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150215140207/http://inbedwithmadonna.ru/post97675540/|trans-title=Pugacheva. Jackson. Madonna.|language=Russian}}</ref>\n \t\nMadonna's very distant [[Rurik dynasty|House of Rurik]] DNA-traced ancestry (through [[Valdemar II of Denmark]]'s mother [[Sophia of Minsk]] and [[Vsevolod I of Kiev]] on his paternal side) was revealed by [[MyHeritage]] during the company's 2019 partnership with [[Eurovision]]. Fun fact was noticed in Russia by the media.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.adme.ru/tvorchestvo-muzyka/20-faktov-o-nepredskazuemoj-madonne-i-ej-snova-udalos-nas-udivit-2147815/|title=20+ \u0444\u0430\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u043e \u041c\u0430\u0434\u043e\u043d\u043d\u0435, \u043a\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0440\u044b\u0435 \u0438\u0437\u0432\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043d\u044b \u0442\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043a\u043e \u0435\u0435 \u0441\u0430\u043c\u044b\u043c \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u043c \u043f\u043e\u043a\u043b\u043e\u043d\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430\u043c|trans-title=20+ facts about Madonna that are known only to her most devoted fans|publisher=ADME.ru|date=August 16, 2019|accessdate=September 14, 2019|language=Russian}}</ref><ref name=\"myheritage\">{{cite web|url=https://www.myheritage.com/eurovision/blog/these-six-eurovision-winners-are-related-to-madonna/|title=These Eurovision Winners Are Related to Madonna|publisher=[[MyHeritage]]|accessdate=June 3, 2019|date=May 17, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190603174607/https://www.myheritage.com/eurovision/blog/these-six-eurovision-winners-are-related-to-madonna/|archivedate=June 3, 2019|language=Russian}}</ref> In a [[High-context and low-context cultures|high-context culture]] (see also another Rurikid, famous classical composer [[Modest Mussorgsky]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.medici.tv/en/artists/modest-mussorgsky/|title=Modest Mussorgsky|publisher=[[Medici.tv]]|accessdate=November 17, 2019}}</ref> and {{ill|List of canonized Russian Princes and Princesses|ru|\u0421\u043f\u0438\u0441\u043e\u043a \u043a\u0430\u043d\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0437\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0440\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0445 \u043a\u043d\u044f\u0437\u0435\u0439 \u0438 \u043a\u043d\u044f\u0433\u0438\u043d\u044c#\u0420\u044e\u0440\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447\u0438}}) the fact has changed local conservative nationalist media's tone and lexics to a more positive one.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tsargrad.tv/news/ona-drugaja-no-ee-albomy-na-ostrie-muzykalnoj-mody-gasparjan-o-kritike-madonny_213062|title='\u041e\u043d\u0430 \u0434\u0440\u0443\u0433\u0430\u044f, \u043d\u043e \u0435\u0451 \u0430\u043b\u044c\u0431\u043e\u043c\u044b - \u043d\u0430 \u043e\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0435 \u043c\u0443\u0437\u044b\u043a\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u043c\u043e\u0434\u044b': \u0413\u0430\u0441\u043f\u0430\u0440\u044f\u043d - \u043e \u043a\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0435 \u041c\u0430\u0434\u043e\u043d\u043d\u044b|trans-title=\"She is different, but her albums are at the forefront of musical fashion\": Gasparyan about criticizing Madonna|publisher=Tsargrad TV|date=August 16, 2019|language=Russian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GQOsiYMtNsM|title=\u0420\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043e\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0442: \u041b\u0438\u0431\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0443\u044e \u043f\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0446\u0443 \u0443\u0431\u0440\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u0438\u0437 \u0440\u043e\u0442\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0440\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043e|trans-title=Russian answer: Liberal singer was removed from radio rotation|date=January 28, 2017|publisher=Tsargrad TV|accessdate=September 14, 2019|language=Russian}}</ref> ''[[Rossiyskaya Gazeta]]'': \"Well, and the song \"[[Madame X (album)|Batuka]]\", the basis for which, obviously, is the same as in [[shamanism|shamanistic]] dances of [[Tuva]], could easily have been sung by our [[Buranovskiye Babushki]]\".<ref name=rg2019>{{cite web|url=https://rg.ru/2019/08/05/madonna-dast-shest-shou-v-evrope.html|title=\u0411\u0430\u044f\u043d \u0434\u043b\u044f \u041c\u0430\u0434\u043e\u043d\u043d\u044b. \u0427\u0430\u0439\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0432 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u043c \u0430\u043b\u044c\u0431\u043e\u043c\u0435 Madame X|trans-title=[[Bayan (accordion)|Bayan]] for Madonna. Tchaikovsky in the new Madame X album|publisher=[[Rossiyskaya Gazeta]]|date=August 5, 2019|accessdate=September 2, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190902183143/https://rg.ru/2019/08/05/madonna-dast-shest-shou-v-evrope.html|archivedate=September 2, 2019|language=Russian}}</ref> However, Madonna music was continued to be reviewed very negatively by Russian critics, this time because of her [[Left-wing politics|left-wing]] political preferences.<ref>{{cite we