{"title_page": "Yonghoon Lee", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Yonghoon Lee\n| image              = \n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \uc774\uc6a9\ud6c8\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1973|11|22|df=yes}}\n| birth_place        = [[South Korea]]\n| citizenship        = Korean\n| alma_mater         = [[Seoul National University]]<br/>[[The New School]]\n| occupation         = Opera singer ([[tenor]])\n}}\n{{Infobox Korean name\n| hangul  = \uc774\uc6a9\ud6c8\n| hanja   = \u674e\u52c7\u52f3\n| rr      = I Yonghun\n| mr      = Ri Yonghun\n}}\n\n'''Yonghoon Lee''' (born 22 November 1973) is a [[South Korea|South Korean]] [[Opera|operatic]] [[tenor]]. He has performed at many of the most prestigious theaters in the world, including the [[Royal Opera House]], Covent Garden, [[Metropolitan Opera]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=3&v=vgsfh4g95gU&feature=emb_title |title=Il Trovatore: \"Ah! s\u00ec, ben mio\" (Yonghoon Lee) at the Metropolitan Opera |accessdate=March 18, 2020 }}</ref>, [[Deutsche Oper Berlin]], [[Vienna State Opera]], [[Rome Opera]], [[Dutch National Opera]] in Amsterdam, [[Bavarian State Opera]] in Munich<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aSfQwTFY-X0 |title=Yonghoon Lee sings \"Nessun dorma\" from TURANDOT at Bayerische Staatsoper |accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref>, [[Teatro alla Scala]] in Milan, [[Semperoper]] Dresden, Lyric Opera of Chicago<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YdstsTGgd84&feature=emb_title |title=Yonghoon Lee - Nessun Dorma from Turandot at the Chicago Symphony Orchesra Hall |accessdate=March 18, 2020 }}</ref>, [[San Francisco Opera]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UoOXm5aVIUI |title=Andrea Ch\u00e9nier Moving Moment #1 - with Yonghoon Lee as Ch\u00e9nier - Fall 2016 at the San Francisco Opera |accessdate=March 18, 2020 }}</ref>, Opera Australia<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Hq5bwwvNFPs |title=OA EXCERPTS: Yonghoon Lee performs 'E Lucevan Le Stelle' from Puccini's Tosca at Opera Australia |accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/newslocal/northern-beaches/yonghoon-lee-a-powerful-tenor-in-sydney-opera-houses-tosca/news-story/1384084b44c734e8a8147e4404baf5e2 |title=Yonghoon Lee a powerful tenor in Sydney Opera House's Tosca |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|accessdate=March 18, 2020|first=Tom|last=Pillans|date=July 9, 2013}}</ref>, amongst others.\n\n==Biography==\nLee studied music at [[Seoul National University]] and [[The New School]].<ref name=royal_opera>{{cite web|title=Yonghoon Lee|url=http://www.roh.org.uk/people/yonghoon-lee|website=The Royal Opera House|publisher=Royal Opera House Covent Garden Foundation|accessdate=17 December 2014}}</ref> He made his international debut in the title role of ''[[Don Carlos|Don Carlo]]'' at the [[Teatro Municipal (Santiago)|Teatro Municipal]] in [[Santiago]], [[Chile]].<ref name=royal_opera /> He made his debut at the [[Metropolitan Opera]] in November 2010 in the same role.<ref name=nytimes_lee>{{cite web|last1=Tommasini|first1=Anthony|title=A South Korean Tenor Makes His Mark at the Met, With La Scala Next|url=http://artsbeat.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/12/20/a-south-korean-tenor-makes-his-mark-at-the-met-with-la-scala-next/|website=The New York Times|publisher=The New York Times Company|accessdate=17 December 2014}}</ref>\n\nHe has shared the stage with some of the most renowned sopranos such as [[Anna Netrebko]].\n\n==Opera roles==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Role\n! Composer\n! Opera\n|-\n| Don Carlo\n| Verdi\n| ''[[Don Carlos|Don Carlo]]''\n|-\n| Manrico\n| Verdi\n| ''[[Il trovatore]]''\n|-\n| Don Jos\u00e9\n| Bizet\n| ''[[Carmen]]''\n|-\n| Radam\u00e8s\n| Verdi\n| ''[[Aida]]''\n|-\n| Don Alvaro\n| Verdi\n| ''[[La Forza del Destino]]''\n|-\n| Calaf\n| Puccini\n| ''[[Turandot]]''\n|-\n| Luigi\n| Puccini\n| ''[[Il tabarro]]''\n|-\n| Cavaradossi\n| Puccini\n| ''[[Tosca]]''\n|-\n| Luigi\n| Puccini\n| ''[[Il trittico]]''\n|-\n| Pollione\n| Bellini\n| ''[[Norma (opera)|Norma]]''\n|-\n| Alfredo\n| Verdi\n| ''[[La Traviata]]''\n|-\n| Rodolfo\n| Puccini\n| ''[[La Boh\u00e8me]]''\n|-\n| Ruggero\n| Puccini\n| ''[[La Rondine]]''\n|-\n| Arrigo\n| Verdi\n| ''La Battaglia di Legnano''\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://zemskygreenartists.com/product/yonghoon-lee/ Yonghoon Lee biography at agent's web site]\n* [http://www.latinospost.com/articles/4758/20120929/metropolitan-opera-review-rachvelishvili-yonghoon-lee-dominate-carmen.htm Metropolitan Opera Review: Rachvelishvili, Yonghoon Lee Dominate Phenomenal Carmen]. Latinos Post.\n* [https://www.operabase.com/artists/yonghoon-lee-18088/en Yonghoon Lee on OperaBase]\n* {{IMDb name|6559498}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lee, Yonghoon}}\n[[Category:1973 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:South Korean opera singers]]\n[[Category:Seoul National University faculty]]\n[[Category:Mannes School of Music alumni]]\n[[Category:Seoul National University alumni]]\n[[Category:21st-century South Korean singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century opera singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Yonghoon Lee\n| image              = \n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \uc774\uc6a9\ud6c8\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1973|11|22|df=yes}}\n| birth_place        = [[South Korea]]\n| citizenship        = Korean\n| alma_mater         = [[Seoul National University]]<br/>[[The New School]]\n| occupation         = Opera singer ([[tenor]])\n}}\n{{Infobox Korean name\n| hangul  = \uc774\uc6a9\ud6c8\n| hanja   = \u674e\u52c7\u52f3\n| rr      = I Yonghun\n| mr      = Ri Yonghun\n}}\n\n'''Yonghoon Lee''' (born 22 November 1973) is a [[South Korea|South Korean]] [[Opera|operatic]] [[tenor]]. He has performed at many of the most prestigious theaters in the world, including the [[Royal Opera House]], Covent Garden, [[Metropolitan Opera]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=3&v=vgsfh4g95gU&feature=emb_title |title=Il Trovatore: \"Ah! s\u00ec, ben mio\" (Yonghoon Lee) at the Metropolitan Opera |accessdate=March 18, 2020 }}</ref>, [[Deutsche Oper Berlin]], [[Vienna State Opera]], [[Rome Opera]], [[Dutch National Opera]] in Amsterdam, [[Bavarian State Opera]] in Munich<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aSfQwTFY-X0 |title=Yonghoon Lee sings \"Nessun dorma\" from TURANDOT at Bayerische Staatsoper |accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref>, [[Teatro alla Scala]] in Milan, [[Semperoper]] Dresden, Lyric Opera of Chicago<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YdstsTGgd84&feature=emb_title |title=Yonghoon Lee - Nessun Dorma from Turandot at the Chicago Symphony Orchesra Hall |accessdate=March 18, 2020 }}</ref>, [[San Francisco Opera]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UoOXm5aVIUI |title=Andrea Ch\u00e9nier Moving Moment #1 - with Yonghoon Lee as Ch\u00e9nier - Fall 2016 at the San Francisco Opera |accessdate=March 18, 2020 }}</ref>, Opera Australia<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Hq5bwwvNFPs |title=OA EXCERPTS: Yonghoon Lee performs 'E Lucevan Le Stelle' from Puccini's Tosca at Opera Australia |accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/newslocal/northern-beaches/yonghoon-lee-a-powerful-tenor-in-sydney-opera-houses-tosca/news-story/1384084b44c734e8a8147e4404baf5e2 |title=Yonghoon Lee a powerful tenor in Sydney Opera House's Tosca |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|accessdate=March 18, 2020|first=Tom|last=Pillans|date=July 9, 2013}}</ref>, amongst others.\n\n==Biography==\nLee studied music at [[Seoul National University]] and [[The New School]].<ref name=royal_opera>{{cite web|title=Yonghoon Lee|url=http://www.roh.org.uk/people/yonghoon-lee|website=The Royal Opera House|publisher=Royal Opera House Covent Garden Foundation|accessdate=17 December 2014}}</ref> He made his international debut in the title role of ''[[Don Carlos|Don Carlo]]'' at the [[Teatro Municipal (Santiago)|Teatro Municipal]] in [[Santiago]], [[Chile]].<ref name=royal_opera /> He made his debut at the [[Metropolitan Opera]] in November 2010 in the same role.<ref name=nytimes_lee>{{cite web|last1=Tommasini|first1=Anthony|title=A South Korean Tenor Makes His Mark at the Met, With La Scala Next|url=http://artsbeat.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/12/20/a-south-korean-tenor-makes-his-mark-at-the-met-with-la-scala-next/|website=The New York Times|publisher=The New York Times Company|accessdate=17 December 2014}}</ref>\n\nHe has shared the stage with some of the most renowned sopranos such as [[Anna Netrebko]].\n\n==Opera roles==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Role\n! Composer\n! Opera\n|-\n| Don Carlo\n| Verdi\n| ''[[Don Carlos|Don Carlo]]''\n|-\n| Manrico\n| Verdi\n| ''[[Il trovatore]]''\n|-\n| Don Jos\u00e9\n| Bizet\n| ''[[Carmen]]''\n|-\n| Radam\u00e8s\n| Verdi\n| ''[[Aida]]''\n|-\n| Don Alvaro\n| Verdi\n| ''[[La Forza del Destino]]''\n|-\n| Calaf\n| Puccini\n| ''[[Turandot]]''\n|-\n| Luigi\n| Puccini\n| ''[[Il tabarro]]''\n|-\n| Cavaradossi\n| Puccini\n| ''[[Tosca]]''\n|-\n| Luigi\n| Puccini\n| ''[[Il trittico]]''\n|-\n| Pollione\n| Bellini\n| ''[[Norma]]''\n|-\n| Alfredo\n| Verdi\n| ''[[La Traviata]]''\n|-\n| Rodolfo\n| Puccini\n| ''[[La Boh\u00e8me]]''\n|-\n| Ruggero\n| Puccini\n| ''[[La Rondine]]''\n|-\n| Arrigo\n| Verdi\n| ''La Battaglia di Legnano''\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://zemskygreenartists.com/product/yonghoon-lee/ Yonghoon Lee biography at agent's web site]\n* [http://www.latinospost.com/articles/4758/20120929/metropolitan-opera-review-rachvelishvili-yonghoon-lee-dominate-carmen.htm Metropolitan Opera Review: Rachvelishvili, Yonghoon Lee Dominate Phenomenal Carmen]. Latinos Post.\n* [https://www.operabase.com/artists/yonghoon-lee-18088/en Yonghoon Lee on OperaBase]\n* {{IMDb name|6559498}}\n\n{{authority control}}